#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/polynomial/chebyshev.py:docstring
#: of numpy.polynomial.chebyshev.chebdiv:37
msgid ""
"In general, the (polynomial) division of one C-series by another results in "
"quotient and remainder terms that are not in the Chebyshev polynomial basis "
"set.  Thus, to express these results as C-series, it is typically necessary "
"to \"reproject\" the results onto said basis set, which typically produces "
"\"unintuitive\" (but correct) results; see Examples section below."
msgstr ""

